# State Management

## Code

```javascript
const [tasks, setTasks] = useState([])
```

## Why I Used It

I used React's useState hook to store and manage task data throughout the application.

## What It Accomplishes

- Stores task information
- Updates the UI automatically
- Enables task creation
- Enables task deletion
- Enables task status updates

## Business Value

Allows the application to function as an interactive project management dashboard rather than a static webpage.
